Blood cell lab test abnormal AE showing an increase in the number of immature leukocytes in peripheral blood. (in hematology) a predominance of immature leukocytes noted in a differential white blood cell count. It is usually indicative of an infection or inflammation. The term derives from a graph of blood components in which immature cell frequencies appear on the left side of the graph.
